Responsibilities:
1. Actively learn about the basic knowledge and experiments skills
2. Support on the daily experiments, ensure test data quality & update test results in time in regular review meeting.

Qualifications/Requirements:
1. Chemistry, biology, food or related background, experience of basic chemical experiments will be better.
2. Good communication & collaboration spirit


Internship harvest
We can provide
•	Competitive internship salary in the industry;
•	Shuttle bus service covering Shanghai;
•	Take part in various kinds of activities in L’Oréal, such as team building;
•	Delicious lunch and meal allowance;
•	Happy Friday, knock off one hour early;

Work address
L’Oréal China R&I center: No.550,Jinyu road, Pudong district, Shanghai
